Here is the JavaScript code to calculate the factorial of a non-negative integer x, where x is set to 7:

```javascript
let x = 7;
let factorial = 1;

for (let i = 1; i <= x; i++) {
    factorial *= i;
}

console.log("The factorial of " + x + " is " + factorial);
```

This script initializes the variable x with the value 7, then iteratively multiplies numbers from 1 up to x to compute the factorial. The result is printed to the console.
